### Clean Architecture
- Strictly adhere to the Clean Architecture layers: Presentation, Domain, and Data
- Follow the dependency rule: dependencies always point inward (Presentation → Domain ← Data)
- Domain layer contains entities, repository interfaces, and use cases
- Data layer implements repositories and contains data sources and models (DTOs)
- Presentation layer contains UI components and blocs (no view models)
- Entities are pure domain objects (no Flutter imports, no business workflows)
- Use cases hold business rules; repositories orchestrate data sources
- Use proper abstractions with interfaces/abstract classes for each component
- Every feature should follow this layered architecture pattern
- Presentation and BLoC must depend on domain entities, never on data models
